description: Filters referring to tiddler titles beginning with `::` must now quote them
impact-type: compatibility-break

Before v5.5.0, a bare word beginning with `::` in a filter was treated as a tiddler title. From v5.5.0 onwards it is parsed as a [[filter pragma|Filter Pragmas]], and an unknown pragma name causes the filter to return an error.

A tiddler title beginning with `::` must now be written within double square brackets, e.g. `[[::my title]]`.
